write_lef_library(25.10)                              write_lef_library(25.10)

Name
       write_lef_library  -  The write_lef_library command facilitates compar-
       isons between LEF-based input and OpenAccess-based input

Syntax
       write_lef_library

       [-help]

       [<filename>]

       [-all_auto_generated_via | -macro_only ]

       [-lef_layer_order]

       [-macro_only [-no_property]]

       [-tech_only | -macro_only]

       [-tech_only | -macro_list <string>]

       [-use_spacing_table_default]

       Writes the LEF library data (composed of technology  data  and  macros)
       that is present in the Innovus database.

       The write_lef_library command facilitates comparisons between LEF-based
       input and OpenAccess-based input. LEF allows cases where VIARULE GENER-
       ATE  has  WIDTH  specified for either the top or bottom layer. However,
       such cases are not supported by the OpenAccess tech. To make  the  com-
       parison   between   LEF-based   and   OpenAccess-based   input  easier,
       write_lef_library dumps "WIDTH 0 TO 1000 ;" for  any  VIARULE  GENERATE
       that does not have WIDTH specified in the original LEF.

       The Innovus database being read should not have any encrypted LEF file.
       If  an encrypted LEF file is detected, write_lef_library reports an er-
       ror and stops.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each write_lef_library parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man write_lef_library.

       <fileName>
              Specifies the output LEF file name.

       -all_auto_generated_via
              Includes all auto generated vias from the generateVias command.

       -lef_layer_order
              Writes  out  only the layers specified in the lefLayerOrder con-
              straint.

       -macro_list <string>
              Writes the macros specified in the macro list.

       -macro_only
              Writes only the macro data to the LEF file.

       -no_property
              Writes data in the LEF file without any properties. This  option
              can be used only with the -macro_only option.

       -tech_only
              Writes only the technology data to the LEF file.

       -use_spacing_table_default
              Replaces  any  spacing  value  that  matches the default spacing
              value with the "-" character in the LEF file.

              When reading spacing tables from a LEF file, lef2oa replaces any
              "-" table entry with the default spacing value. The spacing  ta-
              ble  in  the  OpenAccess  version therefore contains the default
              values for  all  such  entries.  By  default,  write_lef_library
              writes  out  the  actual  values in the spacing table in the LEF
              file.    When    -use_spacing_table_default    is     specified,
              write_lef_library  replaces  any  spacing value that matches the
              default value with the "-" character in the LEF file. This makes
              it  easier  for  you  to  compare  the  LEF  file  generated  by
              write_lef_library with the original LEF file.

Examples
              *

                The  following  command  writes  the  technology data into the
                tech.lef file:

                write_lef_library tech.lef -tech_only

                You can set the LEF version to 5.7 or 5.8 using  lefDefOutVer-
                sion:

                set lefDefOutVersion 5.8

